=head1 NAME

	CL_RFC2308_7_2_cache_dead_server - Caching of dead server indication


=head1 VERIFICATION POINTS

	Verify that a NUT caches a dead server indication

=begin html
	<UL>
	<DD><li>Dead / Unreachable servers are servers that fail to respond in any
        <DD>way to a query or where the transport layer has provided an
        <DD>indication that the server does not exist or is unreachable.  A
        <DD>server may be deemed to be dead or unreachable if it has not
        <DD>responded to an outstanding query within 120 seconds.</li>
<BR>
	<DD><li>A server MAY cache a dead server indication.  If it does so it MUST
        <DD>NOT be deemed dead for longer than five (5) minutes.  The indication
        <DD>MUST be stored against query tuple "query name, type, class, server
        <DD>IP address" unless there was a transport layer indication that the
        <DD>server does not exist, in which case it applies to all queries to
        <DD>that specific IP address.
	</li>
	</ul> 

=end html

=head1 TARGET

	Client (with Caching function)

=head1 SYNOPSIS

=begin html
<PRE>
	<A HREF="./CL_RFC2308_7_2_cache_dead_server.seq">CL_RFC2308_7_2_cache_dead_server.seq</A> [-tooloption ...]: KOI tool option
	See also <A HREF="../DNSConfig.pm">DNSConfig.pm</A>
</PRE>

=end html

